Rxd1 h5 19. Ne4 Nxe4 20. Qxe4 Bb4 21. Qh4 $14 Kb8 22. Qf6 Rg8 23. Qh6 $1 Ng4
24. Qxh5 $16 {1/2-1/2 Sasikiran,K (2633)-Sturua,Z (2565)/Dubai 2002/CBM 087
Extra (50)}) {At this point the main choice of white over the years was 18.
Rxd8 followed by Rd1, gaining control over the d-file. However, this allows
black to bring his queen to f6, where it has a more active role than on c7.
Therefore, I would recommend playing a useful move that does not give black
the opportunity to activate his queen:} 18. e3 $5 {[%csl Gd4][%cal Gd1d4,Gd4a4,
Gd4h4,Ye3d4] This move prepares rook lift to d4 and we know from previous
